Police have launched a hunt for poachers who beheaded 100 deer and left the remains scattered across woodland in Spain.

Horrified ramblers in the Castile and Leon region of central Spain stumbled upon the macabre sight during an afternoon stroll.

Sickened walker Narela Hinojosa, 37, said: 'It was like something out of a horror film.

