A police spokesman said they were now trying to trace the poachers.

A local huntsman Melito Muro Manzanares, 49, said: 'They call themselves hunters but this isn't hunting.

'It is poaching at its most barbaric and it brings the sport a bad name. Keeping down the numbers of deer is important for the environment, but it needs to be done at the right time of year, and in the right way.'

 

